# GraphQL API

{{ project_name }} includes a GraphQL API built with [Strawberry](https://strawberry.rocks/).

## Starting the Server

```bash
uv run uvicorn {{ package_name }}.graphql.main:app --reload
```

## GraphQL Playground

When running, the GraphQL playground is available at:

- **GraphiQL**: [http://localhost:8000/graphql](http://localhost:8000/graphql)

## Schema

### Queries

```graphql
type Query {
  hello: String!
  health: HealthStatus!
}
```

### Types

```graphql
type HealthStatus {
  status: String!
  version: String!
}
```

## Example Queries

### Hello World

```graphql
query {
  hello
}
```

**Response:**

```json
{
  "data": {
    "hello": "Hello from {{ project_name }}!"
  }
}
```

### Health Check

```graphql
query {
  health {
    status
    version
  }
}
```

## Python Client

```python
from gql import gql, Client
from gql.transport.aiohttp import AIOHTTPTransport

transport = AIOHTTPTransport(url="http://localhost:8000/graphql")
client = Client(transport=transport, fetch_schema_from_transport=True)

query = gql("""
  query {
    health {
      status
      version
    }
  }
""")

result = client.execute(query)
```
